<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF73CEA3FCD5FD9ADE6B3F84" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF73CEA3FCD5FD9ADE6B3F84" blockId="254.[810,1452,587,1010]" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FCD5FD9AD8F73E4B" bold="true" box="[810,932,587,613]" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FBC7FD9DDFF33E4B" box="[1080,1184,588,614]" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">A. simoi</emphasis>
(Ríos-Tamayo, 2019, fig. 6 F–H) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF73CEA3FB48FDA1DE1B3EA7" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1207,1352,624,650]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FB48FDA1DE1B3EA7" box="[1207,1352,624,650]" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">A. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF73CEA3FA6CFDA1D88E3E83" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1923" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubiomaculatus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FA6CFDA1D88E3E83" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">A. dubiomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leg distal articles being lighter than the proximal ones but differ from these species and from all other members of the 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF73CEA3FB30FD0DDE643EDB" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1231,1335,732,757]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FB30FD0DDE643EDB" box="[1231,1335,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the smooth rastellum. Females are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF73CEA3FA6CFCD1D88E3F13" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1923" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubiomaculatus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FA6CFCD1D88E3F13" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">A. dubiomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of lateral swellings on the spermathecae receptaculum but are readily recognized by the sub squared receptaculum with poorly developed external lobe (Ríos-Tamayo, 2019, fig. 7 F, G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF73CEA3FCA0FC62DE1C3FE0" box="[863,1359,947,974]" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" type="description">
